FBIS4-48988 "drchi084_v_94020" FBIS-CHI-94-084 Daily Report 28 Apr 1994 TAIWAN Heavy-Industry Exports Set Record in First Quarter Heavy-Industry Exports Set Record in First Quarter OW2804132494 Taipei CNA in English 0814 GMT 28 Apr 94 OW2804132494 Taipei CNA English BFN [By Y. C. Tsai] [Text] Taipei, April 28 (CNA) -- Taiwan's efforts to promote industrial upgrading have paid off as heavy industry exports reached a record high in the first quarter, the Ministry of Economic Affairs reported Thursday [28 April]. Ministry tallies show that Taiwan exported US$108.30 billion worth of heavy industry products in the first three months of 1994, accounting for 53.8 percent of its aggregate exports, which totaled US$201.3 billion. The ratio of heavy industry exports to Taiwan's total outbound shipments represented a 2.5 percent growth from the same period of last year, while total exports increased only 0.4 percent, officials said.
